  "@type": "Article",
  "description": "Somewhere in the emsemioverse we should document the relationship that relationality is formalized as two mathematical systems, semiotic universes and quasicrystalline hypertensor topos. GFRTU is meant to be deprecated — as long as we capture all the ideas from it within the QCHTTopos that superseded it, historically in my research.\nLike, relationality = metaphysical philosophy, but also has its own \u0026ldquo;math\u0026rdquo; represented using S-expressions. Semiotic universes is a simple mathematical object that we can extend into various directions — that\u0026rsquo;s kind of the whole point of \u0026ldquo;semiotics\u0026rdquo; lol.\n",
